      • isCell

        boolean isCell(net.minecraft.item.ItemStack is)
        return true if the provided item is handled by your cell handler. ( AE May choose to skip this method, and just request a handler )
        Parameters:
        is - to be checked item
        Returns:
        return true, if getCellHandler will not return null.

      • getCellInventory

        <T extends IAEStack<T>> ICellInventoryHandler<T> getCellInventory(net.minecraft.item.ItemStack is,
                                                                  ISaveProvider host,
                                                                  IStorageChannel<T> channel)
        If you cannot handle the provided item, return null
        Parameters:
        is - a storage cell item.
        host - anytime the contents of your storage cell changes it should use this to request a save, please note, this value can be null. If provided, the host is responsible for persisting the cell content.
        channel - the storage channel requested.
        Returns:
        a new IMEHandler for the provided item

      • getStatusForCell

        default <T extends IAEStack<T>> int getStatusForCell(net.minecraft.item.ItemStack is,
                                                     ICellInventoryHandler<T> handler)
        0 - cell is missing. 1 - green, ( usually means available room for types or items. ) 2 - orange, ( usually means available room for items, but not types. ) 3 - red, ( usually means the cell is 100% full )
        Parameters:
        is - the cell item. ( use the handler for any details you can )
        handler - the handler for the cell is provides for reference, you can cast this to your handler.
        Returns:
        get the status of the cell based on its contents.

        Returns:
        the ae/t to drain for this storage cell inside a chest/drive.
